        <br>    
        Being based in Barcelona, it means a lot to me to contribute to the growth of local businesses here. Helping a place like Cataluña Cafe thrive in this city is something I take pride in. I want to make Barcelona a little better every day through the work I do. With every website I create, I aim to combine great design with functionality, always keeping the client’s needs at the forefront. For Cataluña Cafe, it was all about making the website a true extension of their space—a welcoming, easy-to-navigate site that connects them with the people of Barcelona and beyond.</p>

        <h2>Headless CMS</h2>

        <p>
            Working with Cataluña Cafe was not just about creating a beautiful website—it was about giving them the tools they needed to manage their online presence easily and effectively. I chose to use a headless CMS for this project, which may sound a bit technical, but I’ll break it down in simple terms.
            <br>   
            A headless CMS (Content Management System) is like a regular CMS, but without the front-end (the part of the website you see and interact with). In traditional systems, the content (like text, images, and videos) is tightly connected to the design of the website. With a headless CMS, the content is stored separately, and we can use any technology to display it however we want. This allows for greater flexibility, faster loading times, and a smoother experience for visitors.
            <br>   
            For Cataluña Cafe, I used WordPress as the headless CMS. It’s still the same easy-to-use WordPress you might be familiar with, where you can log in, add blog posts, update the menu, or change details, but the design and performance of the website are powered by another tool—Astro.js. Astro is a modern technology that makes websites incredibly fast by only loading the parts the visitor needs when they need them. So, the site looks great, works quickly, and customers enjoy a seamless experience.
            <br>   
            What’s great about this approach is that you, as the business owner, don’t need to worry about any of this complexity. You can still update your content through WordPress just like always, but behind the scenes, the website is more flexible, faster, and future-proof. This setup gives Cataluña Cafe the freedom to focus on what they do best—serving great coffee to the people of Barcelona—while the website stays efficient and easy to manage. 
        </p>

